 their lost limbs and deaths as normal. Their families' arts of maintenance and repair illuminate ongoing struggles to survive and remake larger systems of food, land, technology, and medicine.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aDiabeteszBelize. 0aDiabeticsvCase studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aaffliction.  aamputated limbs.  ablood sugar.  acaribbean.  acentral america.  achanging bodies.  acronicas.  adeath.  adiabetes.  aeerie injuries.  afighting disease.  afood.  aglobal history.  aland.  aliving with diabetes.  alost limbs.  amedicine.  apolicy misrecognitions.  apower.  ascience.  aslow moving disease.  aslow moving story.  asugar intake.  atechnology.  aunequal infrastructures.  auntimely deaths.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2019z978311066763940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520969858zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520969858423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520969858.jpg  a978-3-11-066763-9  UC Press eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-SEWb2020